Lisa Monaco, Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, has concluded her visit to Afghanistan. She went to assess the terrorist threat to US, Afghan, and regional interests and discuss ways to enhance counterterrorism efforts. Monaco met with President Ashraf Ghani and conveyed President Obama's appreciation for his leadership, expressed support for an Afghan-led reconciliation process, and emphasized the importance of a lasting relationship with Afghanistan. She also met with US military and civilian leaders and troops to gather their perspectives on the security situation and ideas on maintaining security gains while targeting al-Qa'ida remnants and disrupting terrorist threats. Monaco also took the opportunity to honor the bravery and dedication of US service members and civilian personnel who have worked to keep America safe over the last 13 years.